Fix preprocessor indentation

Indent the C preprocessor directives to reflect their nesting
using the following script:

$ cppi -l $(git grep -El '^[[:space:]]*#[[:space:]]*(if|ifdef|ifndef|elif|else|endif|define|pragma)[[:space:]]' src tests |grep -Ev '\.(sh|test)$') |while read f; do
	cppi < "$f" > "$f".cppi; mv "$f".cppi "$f"
done

tests: fix generated injection tests

All generated injection tests that need scno_tampering.sh should have
their argument list start with --inject=.

This new syscall was introduced by Linux kernel commit v6.8-rc1~176.

lsm_list_modules.
* src/lsm.c (SYS_FUNC(lsm_list_modules)): New function.
* NEWS: Mention this change.

printpidfd: add pidfs support

Linux kernel commit v6.8-rc1-17-gcb12fd8e0dab moves pidfd from the
anonymous inode infrastructure to a new pidfs pseudo filesystem.

* src/util.c (printpidfd): Handle new format of kernel provided
information associated with pidfd descriptors.
* tests/pidfd_getfd-y.c (PIDFD_PATH): Remove.
(PRINT_PIDFD_PATH): Define.
* tests/pidfd_getfd-yy.c (PRINT_PIDFD): Rename to PRINT_PIDFD_PID.
* tests/pidfd_getfd.c: Include "xmalloc.h".
(PIDFD_PATH): Remove.
(PRINT_PIDFD): Rename to PRINT_PIDFD_PID.
(PRINT_PIDFD_PATH): Provide fallback definition.
(main) [PRINT_PIDFD_PATH]: Use get_fd_path() instead of hardcoding
<anon_inode:[pidfd]>.
* tests/pidfd_open.c (main): Use get_fd_path() instead of hardcoding
<anon_inode:[pidfd]>.
* tests/scm_pidfd.c (print_pidfd): Likewise.
* tests/so_peerpidfd.c (print_pidfd): Likewise.

Rename --stack-traces to --stack-trace for consistency

Do not use plural in option names, but retain old option name
for backwards compatibility.

* NEWS: Mention this.
* doc/strace.1.in: Rename --stack-traces to --stack-trace.
* src/strace.c: Likewise. Retain old option for backwards compatibility.
* src/strauss.c: Likewise.
* tests/options-syntax.test: Likewise.
* tests/strace-k.test: Likewise.
* tests/strace-k-with-depth-limit.test: Likewise.
* tests/strace-kk.test: Likewise.
* tests/strace-kk-p.test: Likewise.

Show the slave device for the fd opening /dev/ptmx when -yy is given

An example output:

     read(32</dev/ptmx<char 5:2 @/dev/pts/7>>, "\0\"\\0", 4) = 4

* src/defs.h (struct finfo::tty_index): New member.
(get_finfo_for_dev): Add two parameters.
* src/ioctl.c (SYS_FUNC(ioctl)): Pass pid and fd to get_finfo_for_dev().
* src/utils.c (is_ptmx, set_tty_index): New functions.
(get_finfo_for_dev): Read the tty-index field in /proc/$pid/fdinfo/$fd
and store the value to struct finfo::tty_index.
(printenv): Pass pid and fd to get_finfo_for_dev(). Print the slave
device for the fd opening /dev/ptmx as the counter endpoint.
* tests/dev-pty-yy.c: New file.
* tests/gen_tests.in (dev-pty-yy): New test.
* tests/pure_executables.list: Add dev-pty-yy.
* tests/.gitignore: Likewise.

Signed-off-by: Masatake YAMATO <yamato@redhat.com>

  setsockopt(3, SOL_TCP, TCP_AO_ADD_KEY, {addr={sa_family=AF_INET6, sin6_port=htons(0), sin6_flowinfo=htonl(0), inet_pton(AF_INET6, "::", &sin6_addr), sin6_scope_id=0}, prefix=0, alg_name="hmac(sha1)", ifindex=0, set_current=0, set_rnext=0, sndid=200, rcvid=100, maclen=12, keyflags=0, key="\x42\xe9\xd2\xd3\xd1\xec\x9f\x55\x56\x9c\xd7\x89\x1a\x90\x53\xba\x59\x6d\x5f\x0a", keylen=20}, 288) = 0
  setsockopt(3, SOL_TCP, TCP_AO_ADD_KEY, {addr={sa_family=AF_INET, sin_port=htons(0), sin_addr=inet_addr("127.0.0.1")}, prefix=32, alg_name="cmac(aes)", ifindex=0, set_current=0, set_rnext=0, sndid=200, rcvid=100, maclen=12, keyflags=0, key="\x7a\x66\x25\xc9\x80\xdb\x68\x95\xf5\xaf\x84\x1b\xd6\x50\x29\xe1", keylen=16}, 288) = -1 ENOPROTOOPT (Protocol not available)
